beer.beer_description: Influenced by the early European classics, our brew has been created to celebrate Australianâ€™s love of crisp, refreshing lagers. A combination of Aussie malt & New Zealand hops. The beer is pale straw in colour, the finish is soft, crisp & effortlessly clean.

Influenced by the early European classics, our brew has been created to celebrate Australianâ€™s love of crisp, refreshing lagers. A combination of Aussie malt & New Zealand hops. The beer is pale straw in colour, the finish is soft, crisp & effortlessly clean.

A darker beer fermented at a sligtly warmer temperature. "Pre-prohibition beers" were full of character and flavour as they were brewed using 'Floor-malted' barley - a process that disappeared in the 1920's as maltings became more mechanised. The use of floor-malted grains gives the beer its nutty or bready character, balanced with a generous gift of Czech grown Saaz hops in the kettle.
This new beer is our first made with Nectaron hops, added as a late hop and dry hop addition. It has notes of stone fruit with a bold citrus flavour. Enjoy!

The beer has a crisp clean finish, is very refreshing, perfect to drink with seafood.

This all malt beer is master brewed to exhibit a pronounced hop flavour and aroma. â€‹Influenced by our Master Brewer, we have used four distinct hops to achieve a Hoppy taste. To make the beer more flavoursome we have balanced the beer with several different malts late in the brewing process. â€‹This beer is special, the beer is caramel in colour with medium bitterness.

Marsden Neopolitan Porter - Just like the ice cream, Berry - Vanilla - Chocolate! It's a different take on our usual Chocolate Porter with the three distinct ingredients combining to create a triumvirate of flavour! Try it with a piece of Chocolate Mudcake or maybe just a piece of chocolate!

Inspired by the traditional steam beers of the gold rush era. The thick creamy head, deep amber colour from Pale and Crystal malts, and distinctive hop flavour from the US grown Cascade hops make this a crisp, refreshing beer with plenty of character.
This beer is the first of its kind. A DRY beer brewed in a Craft Brewery. The beer is brewed longer to produce a dry beer with lower carb, medium bitterness and a subtle hop character.
